<h1><span id="Blackburne_Shilling_Gambit">Blackburne Shilling Gambit</span></h1>
<h3><span id="3...Nd4">3...Nd4</span></h3>
<p>Black violates an opening principle by again moving his knight. It may be tempting for White to take the now unprotected pawn with 4. Nxe5 but after 4...Qg5, White is in trouble (though 5. Bxf7+ remains playable). To maintain an advantage, White can play 4. Nxd4, 4. c3 or 4. O-O.
</p>
<p><b>1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nd4</b>
</p>
